Hyenas
>Imperial Dictatorship
They follow the will of the matriarch. Unlike in the noble houses that we're used to they aren't bothered by marriages between different classes. So long as the matriarch keeps their armies strong and leads them well then they're willing to follow her pretty much to the ends of the Earth. Trial by combat, while not necessarily common, does hold much cultural significance to them. Nearly everyone in any position of note is either a battle-hardened warrior or have the training to compete with them. Though this isn't because combat is a requirement for advancement, it's instead because the types with great aspirations are also very driven and devoted. They believe they have an obligation to honor the matriarch by being combat-capable. The same willpower they posses that drives them to aim for high goals simultaneously drives them to serve their matriarch.
>Chaotic Neutral
At a societal level, yes. On an individual level they're more Lawful Neutral. It would take an immense transgression by the matriarch to make them disavow her.

Lions
>Machiavellian Dictatorship
There's constant political intrigue and within the upper echelons at times even more backstabbing than seen by rats. Since such turmoil is the norm, people aren't too miffed about a change in leadership and will generally continue working to strengthen their nation, albeit with their own personal goals still a concern. Anyone who wishes to lead must always be highly cognizant of their situation and trying to think three steps ahead. Luckily for them, their wider population is very removed from the goings on of the political class and as such aren't of much concern.
>Lawful Evil
They have an extremely "might makes right" mindset. The people below them are below them because they deserve to be. If they were fit to do anything but serve than they wouldn't be serving. If the people in charge weren't fit to be in charge then they wouldn't be in charge.

Rats
>Anarcho-Communism
A tame version of it, but this probably is what fits best. They don't so much care for public ownership so much as they don't care enough about private ownership to uphold it. People can still own private property, businesses, and engage in typical worker-employer relationships, but most rats simply don't feel like bothering to do so would be worth their time. Because of this, currency isn't really a thing internally among them. Among themselves they typically engage in bartering. They do posses currency and work with it just fine, but it's something they see as for facilitating trade between themselves and different nations. They have taboos and rough laws that they still follow, but nothing very concrete. They also really couldn't care less about whether or not other people agree with how they operate or if the outsiders do things radically differently so long as said outsiders don't inconvenience them too much.
>Chaotic Evil
I suppose so, but not at all in the way that people typically think of it. They aren't actively malicious most of the time and will help each other out in times of emergency (i.e. they wouldn't leave someone bleeding out in the street). Though as long as they see that someone is helping to resolve the situation then they'll continue about their business. It's also not uncommon for them to see the opportunity cost of backstabbing someone else to be too great of a risk and potentially painting a target on their own back for no good reason and thus don't actually do it all that much. They might seem like just Skaven at first glance, but they really are very different from how the Skaven behave.
